{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Candied Mint","content":["Place sugar in mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Place a piece of baking paper on a flat surface.","Place egg white in mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a bowl. Using tongs, coat each mint leaf lightly in egg white then in reserved sugar. Arrange coated mint leaves on baking paper and allow to dry in a cool, dry place for approx. 24 hours. Reserve remaining sugar and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Cake","content":["The next day, preheat oven to 180°C. Line a spring form cake tin (Ø 24 cm) with baking paper.","Place courgettes in mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place hemp milk, sugar, oil and eggs in mixing bowl then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Add reserved courgettes and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt then mix <b>15 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to prepared tin. Bake for 35-40 minutes (180°C) until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Remove from tin and allow to cool on a wire rack.","Once cool, garnish with reserved crystallised mint leaves and remaining reserved sugar. Serve in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Candied Mint","content":["50 g caster sugar","1 egg white, from large egg","12 fresh mint, leaves only, for garnish"]},{"title":"Cake","content":["350 g courgettes, cut in pieces (approx. 2 courgettes)","120 g hemp milk","200 g caster sugar","100 g oil","2 large eggs","165 g plain flour","45 g cocoa powder","1 tsp baking powder","1 pinch fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r134407","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-B0R8s2F7UPw\/XZWrIbbcXVI\/AAAAAAAAfik\/MOcFPnYfBuQxRkvwnGmb7XBAevk3EPcBQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_cgw1S-yRm24Ozmpb.png","title":"Courgette and Cocoa Cake","publishedAt":"2017-03-27T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"11 g","uom":"per 1 portion","